<h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Business Task</h2>
<p dir="auto">Danny wants to use the data to answer a few simple questions about his customers, especially about their visiting patterns, how much money theyâ€™ve spent and also which menu items are their favourite.</p>
<h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Question and Solution</h2>
<strong>1. What is the total amount each customer spent at the restaurant?</strong>
SELECT s.customer_id,
SUM(m.price) total_spending_per_customer
FROM sales s
JOIN menu m
ON s.product_id=m.product_id
GROUP BY s.customer_id
ORDER BY s.customer_id;
